                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay (<persName type="from"
                            >Wright</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-17T02:00:00-03:30"
                            >July 17, 1932—2 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. My 41, July 16, midnight. Presence here of two United States Coast Guard
                    vessels offers possible opportunity for conference on board between
                    representatives of both Governments. <persName corresp="#p_BRW1"
                        >Bliss</persName> concurs in this suggestion. Please advise whether we may
                    be authorized to propose this to Uruguayan and Argentine Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
